For some value of $x,$ $0 < x < 180,$
\[\tan 53^\circ \tan 81^\circ \tan x^\circ = \tan 53^\circ + \tan 81^\circ + \tan x^\circ.\]Find $x.$
inference:
**Solution:**
\begin{align*}
\tan 53^\circ \tan 81^\circ \tan x^\circ &= \tan 53^\circ + \tan 81^\circ + \tan x^\circ\\
\Rightarrow\qquad \frac{\tan 53^\circ \tan 81^\circ \tan x^\circ}{\tan 53^\circ \tan 81^\circ} &= \frac{\tan 53^\circ + \tan 81^\circ + \tan x^\circ}{\tan 53^\circ \tan 81^\circ}\\
\Rightarrow\qquad \tan x^\circ &= \frac{\tan 53^\circ + \tan 81^\circ}{\tan 53^\circ \tan 81^\circ - 1}\\
\Rightarrow\qquad x^\circ &= \tan^{-1}\left(\frac{\tan 53^\circ + \tan 81^\circ}{\tan 53^\circ \tan 81^\circ - 1}\right)\\
\Rightarrow\qquad x^\circ &= \tan^{-1}\left(\frac{\tan 53^\circ + \tan 81^\circ}{1 - \tan 53^\circ \tan 81^\circ}\right)\\
\Rightarrow\qquad x^\circ &= \tan^{-1}\left(\frac{\tan 53^\circ + \tan 81^\circ}{\cos 53^\circ \cos 81^\circ}\right)\\
\Rightarrow\qquad x^\circ &= \tan^{-1}\left(\frac{\sin 53^\circ \cos 81^\circ + \cos 53^\circ \sin 81^\circ}{\cos 53^\circ \cos 81^\circ}\right)\\
\Rightarrow\qquad x^\circ &= \tan^{-1}\left(\frac{\sin (53^\circ + 81^\circ)}{\cos 53^\circ \cos 81^\circ}\right)\\
\Rightarrow\qquad x^\circ &= \tan^{-1}\left(\frac{\sin 134^\circ}{\cos 53^\circ \cos 81^\circ}\right)\\
\Rightarrow\qquad x^\circ &= \tan^{-1}\left(\frac{\sin 46^\circ}{\cos 53^\circ \cos 81^\circ}\right)\\
\Rightarrow\qquad x^\circ &= \tan^{-1}\left(\frac{\tan 46^\circ}{\cos 53^\circ}\right)\\
\Rightarrow\qquad x^\circ &= \tan^{-1}\left(\frac{\tan 46^\circ}{\sin 37^\circ}\right)\\
\Rightarrow\qquad x^\circ &= \tan^{-1}\left(\frac{\tan 46^\circ}{\tan 53^\circ}\right)\\
\Rightarrow\qquad x^\circ &= 46^\circ\\
\Rightarrow\qquad x &= \boxed{46}.
\end{align*}
Final Answer: $\boxed{46}.$ I hope it is correct.
ground_truth:
Isolating $\tan x^\circ,$ we find
\begin{align*}
\tan x &= \frac{\tan 53^\circ + \tan 81^\circ}{\tan 53^\circ \tan 81^\circ - 1} \\
&= -\frac{\tan 53^\circ + \tan 81^\circ}{1 - \tan 53^\circ \tan 81^\circ}.
\end{align*}From the angle addition formula, this is equal to
\[-\tan (53^\circ + 81^\circ) = -\tan 134^\circ = \tan 46^\circ.\]Therefore, $x = \boxed{46}.$
